18/11/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Greek Deputy Defence Minister Lazaros Lotidhis arrives on a three-day official visit to Bulgaria on Tuesday (18 November).
He and his Bulgarian counterpart, Ilko Dimitrov, will sign a Programme for Bilateral Military Co-operation between their defence ministries and discuss further efforts.
In related news, the defence ministers of the EU member countries agreed Monday to establish a European Defence Agency, which would include all EU candidates.
Bulgarian Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov welcomed the decision.
(BTA, BNR, BTA - 17/11/03)
